This paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for learning representations from electronic health records (EHR). The paper specifically focuses on deep learning approaches for representation learning, which is a common topic in the machine learning community (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for learning representations from clinical notes and biomedical literature, which falls under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential impact of these techniques on healthcare (cs.CY, cs.HC).
